//
// T048: `%IDENT%` macro splices are byte-preserved — the lexer's
// existing token-byte fidelity (cst-shape contract §3) carries
// them through the CST, and the byte-passthrough formatter at
// Phase 2c emits them verbatim. Phase 3+ retains this property
// because the LayoutPlanner treats `IdentSplice` tokens as
// `Doc::Text` leaves (research §7).

// `echo` is preferred over `printf` here because `printf` would
// interpret `%F` as a format specifier (uppercase-F float). After
// lit substitutes `%%FOO%%` -> `%FOO%`, echo emits it literally.

// RUN: echo 'module %%FOO%% {}' | nsl-fmt --stdin | FileCheck %s
// CHECK: module %FOO% {}
